I've used multipurpose grease on the little plastic pieces that space 
the two plates from each other and haven't had issues.

> (A stuck vacuum advance plate at highway cruising might also explain
> oil temp variations, that could not be explained by other
> environmental factor.)

Or worse, excessive head temps leading to excessive detonation!
